.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-5-20::.
City: berlin, liverpool, prague, new-york
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, ship, skateboard, snowmobile
1. the person traveling to liverpool is somewhere to the left of the person driving the ship##5
2. the person traveling to berlin is on the right of the person driving the snowmobile##1
3. the person driving the skateboard is in an odd position##4
4. the person driving the car is somewhere to the right of the person driving the ship##5
5. the person traveling to liverpool is somewhere to the left of the person driving the snowmobile##5
6. the person traveling to berlin is between the person traveling to new-york and the person driving the car##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |     2      |     3     |     4      |
| City        | liverpool     | new-york | berlin | prague |
| Transport   | skateboard | snowmobile | ship      | car        |

 